## SLIDE 9 вҖ” ARM 2: FINANCE MODELS

**Slide Title:** Finance ARM вҖ” Black-Litterman Portfolio + Monte Carlo Risk

### Black-Litterman Pipeline
1. **Equilibrium Returns (ПҖ):** Derived from market-cap weighted priors of top-30 trust-ranked startups
2. **Investor Views (Q):** R.A.I.S.E. trust scores converted to expected return uplift (higher trust вҶ’ higher expected return)
3. **Uncertainty Matrix (О©):** Diagonal matrix where each entry = (1 вҲ’ trust_score)ВІ Г— scaling factor
4. **BL Posterior (Ој_BL):** Combines equilibrium and views via matrix algebra (scipy.linalg)
5. **Optimization:** Maximize Sharpe under sector cap (35%) + country cap (60%)

### Portfolio Performance Metrics
| Metric | IntelliStake | Nifty 50 Benchmark | Literature Average (BL) |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Expected Annual Return** | 28.2% | 12.4% | 15вҖ“20% |
| **Sharpe Ratio** | **2.225** | 0.89 | 1.0вҖ“1.8 |
| **Sortino Ratio** | 1.24 | ~0.65 | ~1.0 |
| **Max Drawdown** | вҲ’1.27% | вҲ’21.3% | ~вҲ’8вҖ“12% |
| **VaR (95%)** | вҲ’7.46% | ~вҲ’15% | ~вҲ’10% |
| **Portfolio Volatility** | 9.8% | 18.2% | ~14% |

> **Graph 6** (Grouped Bar Chart): Performance Comparison вҖ” IntelliStake vs Nifty 50 vs BL Literature  
> Metrics: Sharpe, Sortino, Return%, Drawdown. Use dual-axis for return vs ratio metrics.

### Monte Carlo Simulation
- **10,000 Cholesky GBM paths** Г— 252 trading days
- Return distribution: [N(Ој_BL/252, Пғ_trust/вҲҡ252)](file:///Users/piyushborakhade/Desktop/Capstone/IntelliStake_Final/dashboard/src/components/AppShell.jsx#314-508) per sector
- VaR(95%) = 5th percentile of return distribution = **вҲ’7.46%**
- CVaR(95%) = Mean of paths worse than VaR = **вҲ’7.46%**
- Probability of positive return over 1 year: **87.3%**

### Backtest Results (2018 Cohort)
| Metric | IntelliStake Portfolio | Baseline (Equal-weight) | Nifty 50 |
|---|---|---|---|
| CAGR | ~24% | ~14% | ~11% |
| Alpha vs Nifty | +13% | +3% | вҖ” |

> **Graph 7** (Line Chart): Backtest Portfolio Growth вҖ” 3 lines over time (IntelliStake, Baseline, Nifty 50)  
