## SLIDE 10 вҖ” ARM 3: BLOCKCHAIN IMPLEMENTATION

**Slide Title:** Blockchain ARM вҖ” ERC-3643 Identity + Oracle Bridge + Milestone Escrow

### Smart Contract Architecture
| Contract | Standard | Purpose | Key Innovation |
|---|---|---|---|
| `IntelliStakeToken.sol` | ERC-3643 (T-REX) | Permissioned security token вҖ” only KYC wallets can hold/transfer | AML-compliant transfer restrictions built into token logic |
| `ComplianceRules.sol` | ERC-3643 | On-chain KYC/AML rule engine | Auto-blocks non-registered or non-accredited wallets at transfer time |
| `MilestoneEscrow.sol` | Custom 4-tranche | Fund release gated by oracle signature | No tranche released unless trust_score вүҘ 0.50 AND oracle is signed |
| `TrustOracle.sol` | Chainlink-style | Off-chain вҶ’ on-chain trust score relay | EIP-1559 optimized, signed by authority private key, 90-day cadence |
| `IntelliStakeOracle.js` | Node.js oracle | Signs [(startup_id, trust_score, timestamp)](file:///Users/piyushborakhade/Desktop/Capstone/IntelliStake_Final/dashboard/src/components/AppShell.jsx#165-174) | Cryptographic non-repudiation of all audit decisions |

### Oracle Flow (4-Step)
```
Step 1: R.A.I.S.E. Audit
        Risk Auditor computes trust score for all startups (16 parallel workers)

Step 2: Authority Sign
        IntelliStake backend signs payload: sign(startup_id, score, timestamp)

Step 3: On-Chain Push
        Signed payload submitted to TrustOracle.sol via ethers.js
        EIP-1559 gas optimized

Step 4: Escrow Verify
        MilestoneEscrow.sol verifies: signer == ORACLE_AUTHORITY
        If trust вүҘ 0.50 вҶ’ TRANCHE_RELEASED
        If trust < 0.35 вҶ’ freezeMilestoneFunding()
```

### KYC Identity Registry
- **74,577** startup records scraped from MCA + Web
- **50** mock investor profiles (Institutional / HNI / Retail / Non-KYC)
- **1,247** oracle TXs simulated (1,189 releases / 58 freezes)
- Investor tiers: Institutional (Sequoia, SoftBank) В· HNI В· Retail (KYC verified) В· Non-KYC (wallet locked)

### Comparison with Literature (Blockchain)
| Feature | Deng et al. 2024 | Kreppmeier 2023 | Piper et al. 2024 | IntelliStake |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Oracle Guard | Symbolic/SMT | N/A | ZKP | Cryptographic + AI Trust |
| Token Standard | N/A | ERC-20 / custom | DeFi | **ERC-3643 (T-REX)** |
| KYC Depth | N/A | Basic | SSI-ZKP | On-chain AML rule engine |
| Escrow | No | No | No | 4-tranche milestone |

> **Graph 8** (Radar / Spider Chart): Blockchain Feature Coverage Comparison  
> 6 axes: Oracle Security / Token Standard Quality / KYC Depth / Escrow Logic / AML / Automation Level  
> 4 series: Deng, Kreppmeier, Piper, IntelliStake.  
> IntelliStake pentagon should be largest.

